ike the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEdAn","text_ar":"سعدان"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEd","text_ar":"سعد"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riEoYu AlHamaAmi waAlA_ibili","text_ar":"رِعْىُ الحَمَامِ وَالاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb, having berries like myrtle-berries, in which is the least degree of sweetness; not injurious to the camels that feed upon it, but poison to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"venomous"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noxious reptiles or the like, such as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawaAm~","text_ar":"هَوَامّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the decoction thereof blackens the hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Seenà, book ii. p. 252.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n15951","headword_ar":"رَعِىٌّ","root":"rEY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pastured: ruled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarded:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to Golius, as on the authority of the KL; but not in my copy of that work. It is agreeable with analogy as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroEiY~N","text_ar":"مَرْعِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and from it is formed the subst. next following.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}